82. Implement the setcookie( ) function with various arguments using the PHP program.
code:
<?php
// 1. Basic cookie: name and value
setcookie("basicCookie", "HelloWorld", time() + 3600); // Expires in 1 hour

// 2. Cookie with custom path
setcookie("pathCookie", "PathTest", time() + 3600, "/testpath"); 

// 3. Cookie with domain
// Note: Replace "yourdomain.com" with your actual domain if testing on server
setcookie("domainCookie", "DomainTest", time() + 3600, "/", "yourdomain.com"); 

// 4. Secure cookie (only sent over HTTPS)
setcookie("secureCookie", "SecureTest", time() + 3600, "/", "", true); 

// 5. HttpOnly cookie (cannot be accessed via JavaScript)
setcookie("httpOnlyCookie", "HttpOnlyTest", time() + 3600, "/", "", false, true); 

?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>SetCookie Examples</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>SetCookie Function Demonstration</h2>

<?php
echo "<ul>";

// Display cookie values (they will be available on the **next page load**)
foreach ($_COOKIE as $name => $value) {
    echo "<li>$name : $value</li>";
}

echo "</ul>";

echo "<p>Cookies have been set with various arguments. Refresh the page to see them appear.</p>";
?>
</body>
</html>
